name: Nikki Fre$h
overview: Nicole Richie spreads her message of environmental love through her new musical persona, "Nikki Fre$h," a trap music artist who makes eco-conscious choices while dropping sick beats and performing in over the top music videos.

episodes.name: Parent Trap
episodes.overview: Nicole Richie gets a fresh idea that she hopes husband Joel Madden and brother-in-law Benji Madden of MDDN Records can help bring to life.

episodes.name: Let's Get Hive
episodes.overview: Nikki Fre$h gets serious about the role honey bees play in the environment while simultaneously promoting her name and brand to fellow bee lover Bill Nye the Science Guy.

episodes.name: Get Ugly for the Veggies
episodes.overview: Nikki Fre$h does market research and looks for inspiration for her new line of "merch" in the organic produce aisle at the grocery store.

episodes.name: High on Crystal
episodes.overview: In need of some energy healing, Nikki Fre$h visits a crystal store and meets a renowned healer who recommends some helpful gems to promote success in her music career.

episodes.name: Drip So Hard
episodes.overview: Nikki Fre$h visits some of her successful friends to pitch a revolutionary idea - cement water receptacles - that she believes are going to help save the planet.
